//@ compile-fail
//@ error-contains: this cast can fail

// Bare `as` is the always-class of the trichotomy (docs/design/checked-casts.md,
// decision 8): subsumption, widening, newtype wrap/unwrap. A cast that might fail must
// wear its failure policy -- `as?` to test, `as!` to assert -- and spelling it bare is
// a compile error naming both repairs. The runtime halves are pinned in
// cast_triad.neon; the never-class (no overlap at all) stays ImpossibleCast, pinned
// elsewhere.

fn main() {
    let u: i64 | str = 1;
    let n = u as i64;
}
